{
  "stem": "21482.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember anti-Semitism as long as I can remember, from what my parents would tell me, from what my grandparents would tell me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were telling me about pogroms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I always remembered the feeling he would get from-- from the Polish people, always some kind of a remark and always feeling like you don't belong.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents were-- my grandparents were telling me of the pogroms, which happened, you know, years ago, years before in-- in Poland, in Russia, how people had to-- were murdered, people had to emigrate, and how being a-- being Jewish in Poland, we never felt that we belonged, even though they lived there for, you know, for hundreds of years.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we never-- the Polish people never made us feel like we belonged, even though the Jewish people were very patriotic, like during the First War.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncles, my grandfathers, they were all in the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my oldest uncle, my mother's oldest brother, was a surgeon during the first war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was killed on a battlefield.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was awarded one of the highest medals that Poland had to offer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my grandparents were very proud of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Zigmund.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all I-- I have picture of-- I had pictures of him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I used to take the medal to school for show and tell.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it was-- he-- he was killed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very proud of him, because I guess he was so smart, and he was able to go to school and become a doctor.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then he was killed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember in 1937-- you mean the Second War, by the way?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah. 1937, I remember hearing talk about Hitler.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
